    <h3 id="irregular"> Irregular Verbs </h3>
      <p>Now we get to the fun ones, <em><strong>irregular verbs!</em></strong>
        <br><br> These verbs don't follow a large, overarching pattern, which is why we call them irregular.
        Many of the most common verbs that you will use are irregular, such as être (to be), avoir (to have), aller (to go), and faire (to make/do).
      </p>
      <p> For many of these, and indeed even the ones we just mentioned, you will have to memorize their patterns.
        Luckily,  there are various "sub-patterns" that some of the verbs follow, which make them a little easier to memorize.
      </p>
